Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the concept of effective length of codes in distributed transmission over channels with feedback, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of distributed communication systems, which is a key area of research in networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper explores the role of correlation and coordination between distributed terminals in communication systems, which is a topic of interest in social and information networks. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve computational complexity analysis of the coding strategies used in the communication system. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may involve the transmission of multimedia data over the communication system, which is a topic of interest in multimedia research.
